        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 8:24AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 824 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 8 miles northeast of Olney to near
Throckmorton. Movement was south at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Throckmorton, Woodson, Elbert, and Us-183 Near The Throckmorton-
Baylor County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
